parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wiring Harness Insulation Failure in Engine Compartment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness insulation in the engine compartment can cause multiple electrical system failures, leading to engine stalling, fires, and explosions, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: wisps of foul-smelling smoke issuing from the steering column
smoke coming from under the hood
vehicle cutting off completely while traveling at any speed
and fires engulfing the passenger compartment and cargo area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration when Shifting into Reverse
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration when shifting into reverse can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle or surrounding property, posing a significant risk to the driver and others.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates backwards when shifting into reverse gear
often resulting in loss of control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained ignition of the vehicle can cause a total loss of the vehicle, and potentially harm people in the surrounding area.
symptoms: The vehicle is found on fire
with no apparent cause or warning signs
resulting in significant damage or total loss of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mounts can cause excessive vibration, which can lead to premature wear on other engine components, decreased fuel efficiency, and a rough ride for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: which can be felt through the steering wheel
